{
  "updated_summary": "The video segment begins with closing credits over abstract, textured backgrounds shifting between deep blues and intense reds, resembling ink or blood splatters, accompanied by a sustained, eerie, high-pitched synth drone, subtle rhythmic electronic percussion, and a low, resonant synth bass line, punctuated by bell-like synth chimes. White serif text lists production roles including Executive Producer Michael Green, Director Jane Wu, and cast members Masaki Okano as Kenzo and Brendal Spark as Hishamondo, alongside technical and creative team credits. As the credits conclude, the screen transitions to a clean white background featuring the 3 ARTS ENTERTAINMENT logo, followed by a vibrant, multicolored vertical stripe pattern. This pattern resolves into the Netflix logo—a bold red 'N' inside a black circle on a dynamic red and black background with the word 'SUBSCRIBE' beneath it—as the atmospheric music fades out, replaced by a brief piano-like melody and a quick "whoosh" or "ding" sound. The segment then shifts to a static, bold graphic of the Netflix logo on the left, set against deep red and black diagonal gradients, with 'SUBSCRIBE' in white sans-serif font below, accompanied by complete silence."
}
